import pyautogui
import time
import uiautomation as auto

try:
    # Press Windows key to open Start menu
    pyautogui.press('win')
    time.sleep(0.5)
    # Type WhatsApp
    pyautogui.write('whatsapp', interval=0.1)
    time.sleep(0.5)
    # Press Enter to launch
    pyautogui.press('enter')
    # Wait a moment for the window to appear
    time.sleep(2)
    # Confirm WhatsApp window exists
    whatsapp = auto.WindowControl(searchDepth=1, ClassName='Chrome_WidgetWin_1')
    if not whatsapp.Exists():
        raise Exception("WhatsApp window not found after launch")
    print("EXECUTION_SUCCESS")
except Exception as e:
    print("FAILED: " + str(e))
